oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Selections from Eddy Arnold's Folk Song Book album - 1963-10-09
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Performances of Green Green, Where Have All The Flowers Gone, The Folk Singer, The Young Land, and Molly from Eddy Arnold's album, Folk Song Book. Performers include Eddy Arnold (vocals), Chet Atkins (guitar), Ray Edenton (guitar), Jerry Kennedy (guitar), Henry Strzelecki (bass), Harold Bradley (drums), Layne (vibes), and the Needmore Creek Singers (background vocals). Produced by Chet Atkins, engineered by Bill Porter, and recorded on October 9, 1963 at RCA Victor Studio in Nashville, Tenn.
